    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="680"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">782.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/12–2851:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-28T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 28, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>578. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 552, Dec 26.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d680fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Asst Secy Gen for Econ Affs <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d680fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_ZFR1">Fatin Zorlu</persName>.</note> stated this
                    afternoon that <gloss target="#t_GNA1">GNA</gloss> has given <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> auth conclude negots and sign exchange
                        <gloss target="#t_MSA1">MSA</gloss> notes. As result discussions today with
                        <persName corresp="#p_ZFR1">Zorlu</persName> full agrmt with one exception
                    now reached on text Emb note and supplementary <hi rend="italic"
                        >aide-mémoire</hi>. Exception concerns (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) of last
                    para <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 552. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> expresses strong preference for substitution “agreement” for
                    “consultation”. Unless important reasons exist against this substitution, would
                    Dept please instruct urgently whether it wld agree to have (<hi rend="italic"
                        >b</hi>) read: “No conversion into other currencies will occur without
                    taking the Turk foreign exchange position into acct and with prior agreement of
                    the Turk Govt”. If this change cannot be made please supply Embassy with such
                    argument as there may be in order that the necessity of using the word
                    “consultation” can be explained in full and satisfactory detail to <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Turk objection re para 5 of draft note has been met by insertion phrase reading
                    “for the resettlement of refugees within Turk and for” after “include
                    expenditure” as was suggested in second para <gloss target="#t_reftel1"
                        >reftel</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
